{
  "texts": [
    "Instead of directly learning s θ (x, t): R d × [t 0, T] → R d on the whole time interval, we consider to learn s θ (x, t) separately at each time sub-interval in a time-discrete way.",
    "Let t 0 < • • • < t n = T with ∆t = (T -t 0)/n.",
    "For each [t i-1, t i], 1 ≤ i ≤ n, we use one neural network function of the variable x only, denoted by s θi (•): R d → R d, to approximate the continuous-time score function s θ (•, t) restricted in this sub-interval.",
    "1 Accordingly, f θi (x), 1 ≤ i ≤ n, is defined via (3.10) too.",
    "This piece-wise approximation in time domain introduces a time-discretization error which is proportional to ∆t and can be controlled with a small time step size."
  ]
}